to the editor re bob herbert 's recent columns april 17 20 and 24 about the investigation and prosecution of detective zaher zahrey mr herbert 's representation that my office persuaded prosecutors in the office of us attorney zachary carter to bring a federal conspiracy case against detective zahrey denigrates the independence of that office the investigation and prosecution of police corruption cases are essential to the integrity of the criminal justice system although this particular case resulted in an acquittal mr herbert 's characterization of the investigation and prosecution by my office and the united states attorney for the eastern district of new york is unfair charles j hynes district attorney kings county brooklyn april 26 2000

